WEBVTT

00:00.258 --> 00:02.581
Praise the Lord, isn't it good to be in God's house today?

00:03.482 --> 00:04.944
Man, I am proud of you.

00:04.984 --> 00:07.308
You got a belly full of turkey, I'm sure.

00:07.348 --> 00:10.993
You've been just downing tons and tons of Christmas cookies.

00:11.353 --> 00:18.122
You've got that Christmas hangover, but yet you put God's first and you showed up, you put God first, you showed up in his house today.

00:18.523 --> 00:24.311
You know, a lot of churches, they started canceling this service and just doing it online only.

00:24.791 --> 00:26.834
But you know, church and the rock were different, aren't we?

00:27.266 --> 00:33.193
You know, I just think it's special to put God first right here at the very last Sunday of the year.

00:33.213 --> 00:34.555
So I thank you for doing that.

00:34.575 --> 00:36.877
You know, it is the last Sunday of the year.

00:36.957 --> 00:38.219
I know a lot of you are excited.

00:38.239 --> 00:39.020
I've talked to you.

00:39.080 --> 00:41.122
Some of you are getting your vision board together.

00:41.162 --> 00:43.145
You're writing all your goals out.

00:43.545 --> 00:45.147
I was talking to some people yesterday.

00:45.187 --> 00:46.989
They went and bought their habit trackers.

00:47.390 --> 00:48.371
They're ready to go.

00:49.232 --> 00:54.418
But today's message is, Dad's blessed me to get to continue on part four, whatever happened to Hope.

00:54.530 --> 00:58.374
I'd like to talk to you, to those of you who are maybe a little bit discouraged.

00:59.456 --> 01:02.879
You think to yourself, you say, you know, last year, Daniel, I did all that stuff.

01:03.320 --> 01:04.942
And you know what, it just didn't work out.

01:05.222 --> 01:07.304
I just seemed to, it just seemed to not work out.

01:07.324 --> 01:10.408
20, 25 really wasn't that great for me.

01:10.968 --> 01:13.211
And I don't know what, what your reasoning may be.

01:13.291 --> 01:16.635
Maybe, you know, the economy, maybe you lost your job.

01:17.175 --> 01:23.122
Maybe, you know, with the government shutdown tariffs, all these different things, maybe you didn't make what you thought you were going to make.

01:23.394 --> 01:27.500
Or maybe you've been having problems in your family.

01:27.680 --> 01:29.523
Maybe you've had problems with your kids.

01:30.024 --> 01:34.109
You expected them to act a whole lot different than they've been acting.

01:34.670 --> 01:41.800
Maybe some of you, you've experienced a health crisis of some sort where the doctor came to you with a report you were not expecting.

01:42.241 --> 01:44.584
And it just really shook your world.

01:45.606 --> 01:47.228
I know I've got some people in my own family.

01:47.288 --> 01:49.251
They've experienced the death of a loved one.

01:49.271 --> 01:51.314
There's been others that have had a miscarriage.

01:51.682 --> 01:59.051
And you know, you just feel like, man, at 2025, I thought it was gonna be awesome, but it turned out being what I thought was the complete opposite.

01:59.672 --> 02:02.516
Well, today's message, what I wanna do is I wanna encourage you.

02:03.097 --> 02:06.561
I wanna encourage you and let you know, don't let go of your hope.

02:07.362 --> 02:12.328
Don't lose hope that God is still working and God's gonna do something great in 2026.

02:14.411 --> 02:19.858
You know, Dad said that Bible hope is an expectation that God's best, that God's goodness,

02:19.938 --> 02:21.200
is in our future.

02:21.560 --> 02:22.562
It's ahead for us.

02:23.063 --> 02:24.224
And today you heard him talk.

02:24.245 --> 02:26.688
He said, 2026 is going to be year of what?

02:26.788 --> 02:28.571
Expansion and increase.

02:29.232 --> 02:32.918
And no matter how bad last year was, I just want to encourage you, don't let go of that.

02:32.998 --> 02:35.602
Expansion means going beyond our boundaries.

02:36.122 --> 02:39.648
Increase means going further than where we were before.

02:41.190 --> 02:44.695
As I was preparing for this message, I felt like God gave me the word for you.

02:44.996 --> 02:45.597
Come back.

02:47.279 --> 02:49.042
Look at your neighbor and say, come back.

02:50.114 --> 02:52.119
Look at your other neighbor say, come back.

02:53.562 --> 02:56.429
I don't know about you, but I love a good comeback story.

02:56.830 --> 03:00.378
You know, when I was young, there was a movie I loved.

03:00.418 --> 03:01.882
It was called The Crotty Kid.

03:02.042 --> 03:03.265
Anybody remember The Crotty Kid?

03:03.907 --> 03:05.511
It was the original Crotty Kid.

03:05.551 --> 03:08.658
You know, I know there's been all these other ones and Netflix and all this stuff since then.

03:08.770 --> 03:11.233
But you know, the original karate kid, such a great story, right?

03:11.253 --> 03:13.355
It's a bit of a hero's journey, if you recall.

03:13.675 --> 03:15.738
You got this kind of skinny, awkward kid.

03:15.778 --> 03:18.300
He moves to a whole new city, right?

03:18.321 --> 03:19.462
And he just doesn't fit in.

03:19.502 --> 03:20.983
His mom is a single mom.

03:21.344 --> 03:22.005
He's poor.

03:22.365 --> 03:23.746
And he gets kind of picked on.

03:23.807 --> 03:24.627
He gets bullied.

03:24.647 --> 03:25.548
He gets knocked around.

03:25.629 --> 03:28.492
He experiences all kinds of pain set back, right?

03:28.532 --> 03:31.335
He likes this girl, but he doesn't have a chance at all, right?

03:32.016 --> 03:32.696
But what happens?

03:32.756 --> 03:34.979
He doesn't begin to blame other people, right?

03:35.660 --> 03:37.842
He doesn't sit around and make excuses, right?

03:38.114 --> 03:41.218
He finds Mr. Miyagi, right?

03:41.659 --> 03:42.320
And what does he do?

03:42.340 --> 03:43.401
He begins to train.

03:43.481 --> 03:48.027
He begins to let that pressure, all that bad experience push him to get better.

03:48.568 --> 03:51.151
He begins to see all his circumstances, right?

03:51.171 --> 03:53.354
As something that's making him into a champion.

03:53.374 --> 03:53.855
What happens?

03:54.095 --> 03:54.996
He works hard.

03:55.397 --> 03:56.798
He doesn't let go of his hope.

03:57.199 --> 03:59.302
And if you remember the story in the end, right?

03:59.542 --> 04:02.326
He ends up winning the tournament, getting the trophy, right?

04:02.366 --> 04:03.287
The karate tournament.

04:03.667 --> 04:05.650
He ends up getting the girl, right?

04:05.858 --> 04:07.500
Beaten Johnny, right?

04:07.580 --> 04:08.200
The bad guy.

04:08.240 --> 04:11.263
And then he gets one of Mr. Miyagi's really cool cars.

04:11.283 --> 04:11.944
Do you remember that?

04:12.725 --> 04:14.206
He never lost hope.

04:14.226 --> 04:15.507
I love comeback stores.

04:15.608 --> 04:18.570
You know, I believe God loves comeback stores.

04:19.772 --> 04:26.078
Those of you that feel like 2025 was a dud that all the things you were expecting that you were believing to happen didn't happen.

04:26.478 --> 04:31.263
I'm getting ready to tell you, God has a comeback story for you in 2026.

04:31.603 --> 04:32.764
But you got to believe it.

04:33.465 --> 04:34.386
Do you believe it?

04:35.426 --> 04:46.400
You know, so many times we get tired, we get hit on all sides, we go through all kinds of pressure, problems, stress, we got this to do and that to do, and we don't even recognize when we get out of faith.

04:47.261 --> 04:56.232
We don't even recognize that we've lost that active faith, that active believing that God still wants to do good things from me, that God still wants to do good things for you.

04:56.832 --> 05:00.157
The Bible's full of all kinds of these comeback stories.

05:00.177 --> 05:02.740
One of my favorite growing up was the story of Joseph.

05:02.800 --> 05:04.562
You guys remember Joseph in the Bible?

05:05.634 --> 05:08.577
Joseph was his father's favorite son, right?

05:08.737 --> 05:10.619
And as a result, he got all kinds of perks.

05:10.659 --> 05:12.080
He got all kinds of privileges.

05:12.681 --> 05:16.244
And boy, his dad just showered him with all kinds of love.

05:16.505 --> 05:17.966
Joseph was a pretty good kid, right?

05:18.006 --> 05:19.407
Didn't get into trouble much.

05:19.988 --> 05:26.014
But as a result of all this kind of favor he got from his father, his brothers, they were envious, right?

05:26.214 --> 05:26.995
They were jealous.

05:27.515 --> 05:29.297
And if you recall in the story, what do they do?

05:29.637 --> 05:31.419
They sell him into slavery, right?

05:31.940 --> 05:32.880
Now think about that.

05:32.981 --> 05:34.482
Joseph, he serves God.

05:35.170 --> 05:36.231
He's a good guy.

05:36.872 --> 05:37.453
What happens?

05:37.613 --> 05:40.316
He still, he experiences trouble.

05:40.376 --> 05:41.657
He experiences trauma, right?

05:41.677 --> 05:43.660
He gets sold into slavery.

05:44.080 --> 05:47.444
And then even after he's been in slavery for a while, right?

05:47.464 --> 05:48.325
He gets promoted.

05:48.385 --> 05:49.647
He thinks things are looking up.

05:49.987 --> 05:50.548
What happens?

05:51.329 --> 05:53.231
Somebody at his job lies about him.

05:54.252 --> 05:55.433
They slander him, right?

05:55.734 --> 05:58.016
And what he gets thrown back into prison, right?

05:58.677 --> 06:01.761
It seems like every time he starts to make a step forward, what happens?

06:01.781 --> 06:02.962
He gets pulled back.

06:03.842 --> 06:06.925
Kind of like some of you feel that 2025 was, but guess what?

06:07.306 --> 06:09.408
Joseph, he never lost hope.

06:10.089 --> 06:12.151
Joseph was a prisoner of hope.

06:12.692 --> 06:16.556
You never see in these scriptures during all this story where Joseph says, you know what?

06:16.896 --> 06:18.498
This God stuff, it doesn't work.

06:19.319 --> 06:21.762
I think I'm gonna try out these idols of the Egyptians.

06:22.563 --> 06:23.023
Or you know what?

06:23.344 --> 06:24.245
God's forgotten me.

06:24.265 --> 06:26.847
I'm just gonna, this is all I have in life.

06:26.868 --> 06:28.269
I'm just gonna stay in prison.

06:28.629 --> 06:29.450
I'm just gonna be here.

06:29.470 --> 06:30.872
You know, I got a pretty good job.

06:31.132 --> 06:32.754
No, he kept believing.

06:33.154 --> 06:36.397
that what God had said over him was gonna come to pass.

06:36.757 --> 06:43.664
He saw his circumstances as being orchestrated by God that they were preparing him to be a king, right?

06:44.244 --> 06:52.332
It says in Psalms 105 verse 19, until the time came to fulfill his dreams, the Lord was testing Joseph's character.

06:53.253 --> 06:56.736
Joseph believed that God was arranging all these different things for his good.

06:57.477 --> 06:59.078
And you know what, he kept hold of that.

06:59.499 --> 07:03.122
He was a prisoner of hope, and you know what happened eventually,

07:03.202 --> 07:10.374
Joseph was elevated to the second most powerful person in the entire kingdom of Egypt.

07:10.975 --> 07:11.956
He got the gold.

07:12.237 --> 07:13.299
He got the palace.

07:14.060 --> 07:15.262
He got his family.

07:15.622 --> 07:16.504
They're new with him.

07:16.524 --> 07:17.546
He's debt-free.

07:18.006 --> 07:20.290
In the middle of a family, he prospered.

07:20.631 --> 07:23.415
In the middle of the worst times, he flourished.

07:24.317 --> 07:25.198
He was vindicated.

07:25.238 --> 07:30.066
He was promoted all because Joseph kept a hold of that hope.

07:30.434 --> 07:34.180
He didn't say, well, you know, 2025 was just, I'm going to get more of the same in 2026.

07:37.064 --> 07:38.386
He was a captive of hope.

07:39.168 --> 07:40.610
Has anybody ever heard that phrase before?

07:40.790 --> 07:42.913
A captive of hope or a prisoner of hope?

07:44.336 --> 07:48.743
What that means is there's nothing that can shake you free of believing that God's a good God.

07:48.783 --> 07:55.153
There's nothing that can shake your confidence that God's got something great in store for you.

07:55.173 --> 07:56.114
And you know what?

07:56.386 --> 08:03.374
God says that when you're a prisoner of hope, when you're a captive of a hope of that kind, that he actually blesses you double.

08:03.535 --> 08:05.056
Did you know that?

08:05.617 --> 08:09.001
When you say, you know, I'm not gonna be moved, I'm not gonna be shaken.

08:09.362 --> 08:13.427
I know it may have been bad in 2025, but 2026 is gonna be better.

08:13.507 --> 08:15.389
I know God was just getting me ready for it better.

08:15.930 --> 08:17.131
God says he's gonna give you double.

08:17.171 --> 08:21.837
Look at this, Zechariah 9, verse 12, it says, come back to the place of safety.

08:21.937 --> 08:23.979
All you prisoners who still have hope.

08:25.141 --> 08:26.322
Do you still have hope?

08:27.426 --> 08:29.709
Church on the rock, come on, do you still have hope?

08:31.531 --> 08:38.218
I promise this very day, I will repay two blessings for each of your troubles.

08:38.238 --> 08:42.063
You get double blessing when you're a prisoner, a captive of hope.

08:44.285 --> 08:50.753
I'm thinking about a precious family in our church, a gentleman named Larry, he volunteers up here all the time.

08:51.454 --> 08:55.378
And this last year, if you looked at Larry's life, you could say to yourself, he'd say,

08:55.458 --> 08:58.482
Boy, 2025 was a rough year for Larry.

08:59.263 --> 09:01.346
Larry experienced a medical crisis.

09:02.467 --> 09:05.611
He had an emergency where he was taken to the hospital and you know what?

09:05.731 --> 09:08.535
The doctor said it didn't look good for Larry.

09:08.715 --> 09:12.240
It looked like, man, you know, he wasn't gonna make it very many days.

09:12.800 --> 09:13.481
But you know what?

09:13.942 --> 09:15.063
Larry had a wife.

09:15.804 --> 09:17.166
It was a prisoner of hope.

09:18.788 --> 09:20.210
Larry's wife, Barb,

09:20.866 --> 09:23.468
She refused to believe what the doctor said.

09:23.529 --> 09:29.034
She believed that God still had a plan for her and Larry, and that the best was ahead for them.

09:29.114 --> 09:30.675
So you know what Barb began to do?

09:31.216 --> 09:32.437
She got on the prayer line.

09:33.298 --> 09:36.361
She got everybody praying and believing in speaking over Larry.

09:36.781 --> 09:40.004
She began to lay hands over Larry in the hospital room.

09:40.485 --> 09:46.150
I heard that she was even in the waiting room, had a prayer meeting going so loud, it was distracting nurses, doctors.

09:46.550 --> 09:47.351
What's going on there?

09:47.371 --> 09:48.492
She was praying in tongues.

09:48.532 --> 09:49.133
She didn't care.

09:49.193 --> 09:50.514
She was a prisoner.

09:50.626 --> 09:51.187
of hope.

09:51.267 --> 09:52.609
She was captive to hope.

09:52.629 --> 09:58.279
She believed no matter what it looked like, God was still working everything together for her good.

09:58.319 --> 10:07.635
One day, Dad and I, we went down to visit Larry, and you know what, as Dad and I just entered that room, we entered kind of a cloud of hope.

10:08.496 --> 10:11.101
We entered kind of a cloud of expectation.

10:11.642 --> 10:16.530
Dad and I, we went over and we talked to Larry, and in the natural, Larry looked not so good.

10:16.866 --> 10:17.507
But you know what?

10:17.687 --> 10:22.875
Larry, in his quiet week voice, he said to dad, he said, this, it shocked me.

10:22.895 --> 10:24.017
Man, it fired me up.

10:24.037 --> 10:27.442
He said, pastor, I'm going to be out of here by Friday.

10:29.245 --> 10:34.653
And dad and I looked at each other and we smile was, wow, Larry was a captive of hope.

10:35.394 --> 10:39.380
Larry refused to believe that his best days were behind him.

10:39.781 --> 10:40.562
And you know what?

10:40.834 --> 10:42.976
In a few weeks, Larry was out of the hospital.

10:43.117 --> 10:44.358
He's totally well today.

10:44.618 --> 10:46.761
And if you see Larry, he looks amazing.

10:46.781 --> 10:48.342
He looks better than before he went.

10:48.643 --> 10:50.304
Come on, give the Lord a big hand clap.

10:54.629 --> 10:55.690
So here's the big idea.

10:56.291 --> 11:01.256
If you and I want to make a comeback in 2026, you have to believe it.

11:01.637 --> 11:04.941
You have to believe that better days are ahead for you.

11:06.082 --> 11:07.023
You have to believe it.

11:08.224 --> 11:09.906
You can't say, I'm too old.

11:11.906 --> 11:13.227
You can't say I'm too poor.

11:13.287 --> 11:17.311
You can't say, man, this person gets all the other, the breaks.

11:17.691 --> 11:21.035
Man, these other people, they're the ones that, you have to believe it.

11:21.115 --> 11:23.737
If you don't believe it, there's no comeback coming.

11:24.978 --> 11:36.729
One of my favorite scripture verses, Psalms 27, 13 through 14 said, I would have lost heart unless I believed that I would see the goodness of the Lord and the land of the living.

11:37.831 --> 11:41.554
Verse 14 goes on to say, wait on the Lord, that's expectation.

11:42.850 --> 11:47.275
Be of good courage, that's expectation, and he shall strengthen your heart.

11:47.716 --> 11:49.578
Wait, I say, on the Lord.

11:51.200 --> 11:53.603
And you might be saying, Daniel, you don't understand, really.

11:53.643 --> 11:54.845
I appreciate you saying this.

11:54.925 --> 11:57.668
Yes, I know I got to believe it, but it's completely illogical.

11:58.109 --> 12:09.042
If you would just see my kitchen table right now, and you see the stack of bills there, or maybe if only you knew the way my kids have been behaving this year, or the doctor's report, or the debt that I have,

12:09.378 --> 12:13.144
You would truly understand that 2026 probably isn't gonna be that good for me.

12:13.545 --> 12:14.226
Well, you know what?

12:15.148 --> 12:17.191
I encourage you to say what David said.

12:17.251 --> 12:19.215
David was surrounded on all sides.

12:19.836 --> 12:20.918
He was facing death.

12:21.519 --> 12:22.601
It looked like it was over.

12:22.661 --> 12:26.227
He was surrounded by Saul's army, but you know what he said in Psalms 42, 11?

12:27.008 --> 12:31.175
He spoke to himself and he said, Saul, put your hope in God.

12:31.215 --> 12:35.122
Saul, put your trust in the Lord, your king.

12:35.458 --> 12:36.359
That's what we have to do.

12:36.379 --> 12:38.222
When we see that stack of bills, you know what?

12:38.303 --> 12:39.865
We have to speak to ourselves.

12:40.446 --> 12:42.489
My God is bigger than that stack of bills.

12:43.491 --> 12:48.359
When we see our kids behaving crazy and, man, we don't know what we're gonna do, you know what we say?

12:49.000 --> 12:51.003
My God's God is all under control.

12:51.524 --> 12:53.246
My son is gonna serve the Lord.

12:53.627 --> 12:56.131
My daughter is gonna be on fire for the Lord.

12:57.433 --> 12:59.717
The Bible tells us that hope is an anchor.

13:00.898 --> 13:03.122
It keeps us steady when the storm comes.

13:03.714 --> 13:07.199
So when you, you might not think, I'm just not one of those positive thinkers, Daniel.

13:07.620 --> 13:08.441
It's more than that.

13:08.481 --> 13:10.304
It's more than just power of positive thinking.

13:10.605 --> 13:16.674
It's actually keeping your life steady in the storm when you have hope that God is turning things around from you.

13:16.734 --> 13:18.697
It keeps you from drifting.

13:20.700 --> 13:24.406
When Tamara and I first got married, we went on a cruise for a honeymoon.

13:24.967 --> 13:28.533
And one of the excursions that one of the stops was snorkeling, you know?

13:28.813 --> 13:29.394
And so,

13:29.474 --> 13:35.582
We were really excited about this, and there on the shore, we put our towels down, put our bags down, our sandals.

13:35.602 --> 13:41.649
That time we got our snorkel on, and we went snorkeling out there, looking at all the beautiful fish and the coral and all this things.

13:42.110 --> 13:43.792
And after about 30 minutes, it was amazing.

13:43.812 --> 13:46.996
I lifted my head up out of the water, and I was surprised.

13:47.236 --> 13:55.206
I thought I hadn't moved at all, but Tamara and I were like way, way far away from our towels and sandals.

13:55.887 --> 13:56.528
What had happened?

13:57.469 --> 13:58.450
We had drifted.

13:59.330 --> 14:01.112
We hadn't realized it, but we had drifted.

14:01.152 --> 14:06.099
The current had taken us further and further away from where I thought we were.

14:06.199 --> 14:09.103
And do you know, that's what happens to a lot of us when we don't have hope.

14:11.305 --> 14:12.847
You might not think it's a big deal.

14:12.907 --> 14:14.209
You know, I'm not even thinking about it.

14:14.469 --> 14:16.252
I just expect the same of the same.

14:16.392 --> 14:18.314
You know, Dan, well, that's not really a big deal.

14:18.675 --> 14:19.997
You actually, you start to drift.

14:20.117 --> 14:20.597
What do you mean?

14:20.617 --> 14:21.218
What do you do?

14:21.238 --> 14:23.181
Some of you started to drift into bitterness.

14:24.783 --> 14:27.346
Some of you have began to drift into negativity.

14:28.738 --> 14:33.963
Some of you, you didn't even notice it, but this last year, man, you just always got to scow on your face.

14:34.083 --> 14:34.904
You began to drift.

14:36.466 --> 14:39.209
So today, I want to encourage you, dream again.

14:39.269 --> 14:41.271
Dream again.

14:41.651 --> 14:47.657
Put on, like Dad said a few weeks ago, the helmet of hope and get back to what God has called you to do.

14:47.997 --> 14:51.081
It doesn't matter how you've messed up what failures you've had.

14:51.101 --> 14:54.664
It doesn't matter what 2025 looked like.

14:54.684 --> 14:56.466
God hasn't finished with you yet.

14:57.890 --> 14:58.671
Do you believe that?

14:58.751 --> 15:00.113
God's not finished with you yet.

15:03.317 --> 15:06.081
Give back to hoping and believing God for the best.

15:06.602 --> 15:07.884
Stop yourself from drifting.

15:08.745 --> 15:10.247
In the Bible, I find it fascinating.

15:10.267 --> 15:11.569
You have this guy, Samson.

15:11.809 --> 15:12.750
You remember that story?

15:13.151 --> 15:14.453
Samson was the strongest guy.

15:14.493 --> 15:16.535
Did all these great feats of strength for the Lord?

15:17.116 --> 15:19.580
But yet, he became ashamed to his parents.

15:20.160 --> 15:22.043
He became ashamed to the nation of Israel.

15:22.103 --> 15:22.564
